{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_014bPUfDNw3CsZTZQqtTPh5N","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CEjs1NhHfrX9G8DNK4zddz","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/agent/workspace/docs/schema.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14365,"cache_read_input_tokens":27885,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":14365,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KnJpccSTYsfRojm9zc6EhF","session_id":"a2b6d02e-3c8e-471d-894d-da47ffea5542","uuid":"29096c21-4787-4a5d-a92c-c885d20de6bb"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CEjs1NhHfrX9G8DNK4zddz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Database Schema\n     2→\n     3→Backflow uses SQLite in WAL mode with foreign keys enabled. The schema is auto-migrated on startup via `internal/store/sqlite.go:migrate()` using `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS` statements.\n     4→\n     5→Connection string: `<path>?_journal_mode=WAL&_busy_timeout=5000&_foreign_keys=on`\n     6→\n     7→## Tables\n     8→\n     9→### `tasks`\n    10→\n    11→Stores Claude Code agent tasks submitted via the REST API.\n    12→\n    13→| Column | Type | Default | Description |\n    14→|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n    15→| `id` | `TEXT` | — | **Primary key.** ULID with `bf_` prefix (e.g. `bf_01KKQW82994E87Z99QVEMBN8V0`). |\n    16→| `status` | `TEXT` | `'pending'` | Task lifecycle state. One of: `pending`, `provisioning`, `running`, `completed`, `failed`, `interrupted`, `cancelled`. |\n    17→| `repo_url` | `TEXT` | — | Git repository URL to clone (required). |\n    18→| `branch` | `TEXT` | `''` | Branch to check out before running the agent. |\n    19→| `target_branch` | `TEXT` | `''` | Base branch for PR creation (e.g. `main`). |\n    20→| `prompt` | `TEXT` | — | The instruction given to Claude Code (required). |\n    21→| `context` | `TEXT` | `''` | Additional context appended to the prompt. |\n    22→| `model` | `TEXT` | `''` | Claude model override (e.g. `claude-sonnet-4-20250514`). |\n    23→| `effort` | `TEXT` | `''` | Agent effort level. One of: `low`, `medium`, `high`, `xhigh`, or empty for default. |\n    24→| `max_budget_usd` | `REAL` | `0` | Maximum spend in USD. 0 = unlimited. |\n    25→| `max_runtime_min` | `INTEGER` | `0` | Maximum wall-clock runtime in minutes. 0 = unlimited. |\n    26→| `max_turns` | `INTEGER` | `0` | Maximum agent conversation turns. 0 = unlimited. |\n    27→| `create_pr` | `INTEGER` | `0` | Boolean (0/1). Whether to create a pull request on completion. |\n    28→| `self_review` | `INTEGER` | `0` | Boolean (0/1). Whether the agent self-reviews before finishing. |\n    29→| `pr_title` | `TEXT` | `''` | Pull request title (if `create_pr` is set). |\n    30→| `pr_body` | `TEXT` | `''` | Pull request body/description. |\n    31→| `pr_url` | `TEXT` | `''` | URL of the created PR (populated after completion). |\n    32→| `allowed_tools` | `TEXT` | `'[]'` | JSON array of allowed Claude Code tool names. |\n    33→| `claude_md` | `TEXT` | `''` | Custom CLAUDE.md content injected into the agent container. |\n    34→| `env_vars` | `TEXT` | `'{}'` | JSON object of environment variables passed to the container. |\n    35→| `instance_id` | `TEXT` | `''` | EC2 instance ID where the container runs. |\n    36→| `container_id` | `TEXT` | `''` | Docker container ID on the assigned instance. |\n    37→| `retry_count` | `INTEGER` | `0` | Number of times this task has been re-queued (e.g. after spot interruption). |\n    38→| `cost_usd` | `REAL` | `0` | Tracked cost in USD. |\n    39→| `error` | `TEXT` | `''` | Error message if the task failed. |\n    40→| `created_at` | `TEXT` | — | RFC 3339 timestamp. When the task was created. |\n    41→| `updated_at` | `TEXT` | — | RFC 3339 timestamp. Last modification time. |\n    42→| `started_at` | `TEXT` | `NULL` | RFC 3339 timestamp. When the agent container started. Nullable. |\n    43→| `completed_at` | `TEXT` | `NULL` | RFC 3339 timestamp. When the task reached a terminal state. Nullable. |\n    44→\n    45→**Indexes:**\n    46→- `idx_tasks_status` on `status` — used by the orchestrator to find pending/running tasks.\n    47→- `idx_tasks_created` on `created_at` — used for ordered listing.\n    48→\n    49→### `instances`\n    50→\n    51→Tracks EC2 spot instances managed by the orchestrator.\n    52→\n    53→| Column | Type | Default | Description |\n    54→|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n    55→| `instance_id` | `TEXT` | — | **Primary key.** AWS EC2 instance ID (e.g. `i-0abc123def456`). |\n    56→| `instance_type` | `TEXT` | — | EC2 instance type (e.g. `c6g.2xlarge`). |\n    57→| `availability_zone` | `TEXT` | `''` | AWS AZ (e.g. `us-east-1a`). |\n    58→| `private_ip` | `TEXT` | `''` | Instance private IP address. |\n    59→| `status` | `TEXT` | `'pending'` | Instance lifecycle state. One of: `pending`, `running`, `draining`, `terminated`. |\n    60→| `max_containers` | `INTEGER` | `4` | Maximum concurrent agent containers on this instance. |\n    61→| `running_containers` | `INTEGER` | `0` | Current number of running containers. |\n    62→| `created_at` | `TEXT` | — | RFC 3339 timestamp. When the instance record was created. |\n    63→| `updated_at` | `TEXT` | — | RFC 3339 timestamp. Last modification time. |\n    64→\n    65→**Indexes:**\n    66→- `idx_instances_status` on `status` — used to find running/pending instances for task dispatch.\n    67→\n    68→## Status Lifecycles\n    69→\n    70→### Task statuses\n    71→\n    72→```\n    73→pending → provisioning → running → completed\n    74→                                  → failed\n    75→                                  → interrupted → (re-queued as pending)\n    76→         (any non-terminal)      → cancelled\n    77→```\n    78→\n    79→Terminal states: `completed`, `failed`, `cancelled`.\n    80→\n    81→### Instance statuses\n    82→\n    83→```\n    84→pending → running → draining → terminated\n    85→                  → terminated\n    86→```\n    87→\n    88→## Notes\n    89→\n    90→- All timestamps are stored as RFC 3339 strings, not SQLite datetime types.\n    91→- Booleans (`create_pr`, `self_review`) are stored as integers (0/1).\n    92→- JSON fields (`allowed_tools`, `env_vars`) are stored as serialized TEXT.\n    93→- Schema changes are applied idempotently in `migrate()` — new columns use `ALTER TABLE ... ADD COLUMN` with `IF NOT EXISTS` semantics.\n    94→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KnJpccSTYsfRojm9zc6EhF","session_id":"a2b6d02e-3c8e-471d-894d-da47ffea5542","uuid":"be863e27-36e6-4b65-b5c7-a376e51c1370"}
