{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KnJpccSTYsfRojm9zc6EhF","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture of the repository. Let me compile a comprehensive summary.\n\n## Complete Repository Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Backflow repository. Here's a comprehensive breakdown of every file and directory:\n\n### Root Directory Files\n- **CLAUDE.md** - Project instructions for Claude Code with architecture overview, commands, and design patterns\n- **README.md** - Complete project documentation with quickstart, API reference, configuration, and examples\n- **Makefile** - Build targets: `build`, `run`, `test`, `lint`, `clean`, `docker-build`, `docker-deploy`, `db-status`, `setup-aws`, `deps`\n- **.env.example** - Sample configuration with all environment variables documented\n- **.gitignore** - Ignores `bin/`, `*.db` files, `.env`, `mise.toml`\n- **go.mod** - Go 1.24.1 module definition with dependencies (aws-sdk, chi, sqlite3, ulid, zerolog)\n- **go.sum** - Dependency checksums\n- **prompts.md** - Examples of past and future enhancement prompts\n- **claude_output.log** - Untracked agent output log file\n\n### `cmd/backflow/` - Entry Point\n- **main.go** - Server entry point that:\n  - Loads config from environment\n  - Opens SQLite database\n  - Initializes webhook notifier if configured\n  - Creates orchestrator and HTTP server\n  - Runs both orchestrator poll loop and chi API server concurrently\n  - Handles graceful shutdown on SIGINT/SIGTERM\n\n### `internal/api/` - REST API Layer (chi router)\n- **server.go** - Creates chi router with middleware (RequestID, RealIP, Logger, Recoverer, JSON content-type). Registers `/api/v1` routes for health, tasks CRUD, and logs\n- **handlers.go** - HTTP handlers:\n  - `CreateTask` - Validates input, creates ULID with `bf_` prefix, stores to database\n  - `GetTask` - Retrieves single task\n  - `ListTasks` - Lists with status/limit/offset filters\n  - `DeleteTask` - Cancels running tasks or deletes pending ones\n  - `GetTaskLogs` - Fetches container logs via `LogFetcher` interface\n  - `HealthCheck` - Returns status and auth mode\n- **responses.go** - JSON helpers: `envelope` struct with `{data, error}` fields, `writeJSON`, `writeError`\n- **handlers_test.go** - Tests for all handlers using in-memory SQLite and httptest\n\n### `internal/config/` - Environment Configuration\n- **config.go** - Config struct with all settings:\n  - Mode: `ec2` (default) or `local`\n  - Auth mode: `api_key` (default, concurrent) or `max_subscription` (serial)\n  - AWS settings (region, instance type, AMI, max instances, containers per instance)\n  - Agent defaults (model, effort, max budget, max runtime, max turns)\n  - GitHub token, webhooks, database path, poll interval\n  - `Load()` reads from environment variables with sensible defaults\n  - `MaxConcurrent()` calculates concurrency based on auth mode and instance capacity\n\n### `internal/models/` - Data Structures\n- **task.go** - Task struct with fields:\n  - ID, Status, RepoURL, Branch, TargetBranch, Prompt\n  - Config: Model, Effort, MaxBudgetUSD, MaxRuntimeMin, MaxTurns\n  - PR info: CreatePR, SelfReview, PRTitle, PRBody, PRURL\n  - Execution: InstanceID, ContainerID, RetryCount, CostUSD, Error\n  - Timestamps: CreatedAt, UpdatedAt, StartedAt, CompletedAt\n  - Helper methods: `AllowedToolsJSON()`, `EnvVarsJSON()`\n  - TaskStatus enum: `pending`, `provisioning`, `running`, `completed`, `failed`, `interrupted`, `cancelled`\n  - `IsTerminal()` method for status checks\n  - `CreateTaskRequest` struct with `Validate()` method\n- **task_test.go** - Table-driven tests for validation and status checks\n- **instance.go** - Instance struct:\n  - InstanceID, InstanceType, AvailabilityZone, PrivateIP\n  - Status, MaxContainers, RunningContainers\n  - CreatedAt, UpdatedAt\n  - InstanceStatus enum: `pending`, `running`, `draining`, `terminated`\n\n### `internal/notify/` - Event Notifications\n- **webhook.go**:\n  - `Notifier` interface with `Notify(Event)` method\n  - `NoopNotifier` - Discards all events\n  - `WebhookNotifier` - HTTP POST with JSON, event filtering, 3 retries with backoff\n  - EventType: `task.created`, `task.running`, `task.completed`, `task.failed`, `task.needs_input`, `task.interrupted`\n  - Event struct with type, task_id, repo_url, prompt, message, pr_url, agent_log_tail, timestamp\n\n### `internal/orchestrator/` - Core Orchestration\n- **orchestrator.go** - Main poll loop:\n  - Initializes EC2Manager, DockerManager, Scaler, SpotHandler based on mode\n  - `Start()` runs poll loop every `PollInterval`\n  - `tick()` calls: `monitorRunning()` (status checks, timeouts, completions), `dispatchPending()` (assign tasks to instances), `scaler.Evaluate()`\n  - Handles task completion, failure, cancellation\n  - Tracks container counts per instance\n  - Implements `LogFetcher` interface for API logs\n\n- **scaler.go** - EC2 auto-scaling:\n  - Defines `scaler` interface (`Evaluate`, `RequestScaleUp`)\n  - `Scaler` implementation for EC2: launches spot instances, waits for SSM + Docker readiness\n  - `isSSMReady()` checks SSM agent status\n  - `isDockerReady()` verifies agent image availability\n  - Detects externally terminated instances\n  - Terminates idle instances after 5 minutes\n\n- **docker.go** - Container lifecycle via SSM (EC2) or local shell:\n  - `RunAgent()` builds `docker run` commands with task environment variables\n  - Sets up auth credentials (API key or Max subscription)\n  - Passes GitHub token, custom CLAUDE.md, env vars\n  - `InspectContainer()` checks state, reads `status.json`\n  - `StopContainer()` and `GetLogs()` wrap docker commands\n  - `runSSMCommand()` executes on EC2 instances via AWS SSM SendCommand\n\n- **ec2.go** - AWS EC2 wrapper:\n  - `LaunchSpotInstance()` creates one-time spot instances\n  - Uses launch template or AMI + instance type\n  - `TerminateInstance()` and `DescribeInstance()` wrap EC2 API calls\n  - Lazy-initializes AWS EC2 client\n\n- **local.go** - No-op scaler for local mode (no EC2 management needed)\n\n- **spot.go** - Spot interruption handler:\n  - `CheckInterruptions()` polls running instances for termination signals\n  - `handleInterruption()` marks instance as draining, re-queues running tasks as pending with incremented retry count\n\n### `internal/store/` - Persistence Layer\n- **store.go** - Store interface:\n  - Task CRUD: `CreateTask`, `GetTask`, `ListTasks`, `UpdateTask`, `DeleteTask`\n  - Instance CRUD: `CreateInstance`, `GetInstance`, `ListInstances`, `UpdateInstance`\n  - `TaskFilter` struct for list queries (status, limit, offset)\n  - `Close()` method\n\n- **sqlite.go** - SQLite implementation:\n  - Opens in WAL mode with busy timeout and foreign keys enabled\n  - `migrate()` creates `tasks` and `instances` tables with indexes on status and created_at\n  - All CRUD operations with full field scanning\n  - JSON serialization for `allowed_tools` and `env_vars`\n  - RFC3339 timestamp handling\n\n- **sqlite_test.go** - Tests:\n  - Full task CRUD cycle (create, get, update, list with filters, delete)\n  - Instance CRUD operations\n  - Not-found handling\n  - Uses temp databases with cleanup\n\n### `docker/` - Agent Container\n- **Dockerfile** - Multi-arch image (amd64 + arm64):\n  - Base: `node:20-slim`\n  - Installs: git, curl, jq, Python 3, GitHub CLI, Claude Code CLI\n  - Creates `agent` user, configures git defaults\n  - Copies and runs entrypoint.sh\n\n- **entrypoint.sh** - Agent lifecycle script (334 lines):\n  - Clones repo with depth 50\n  - Checks out target branch, creates working branch\n  - Optionally injects CLAUDE.md content\n  - Runs Claude Code with retries (up to 3 attempts)\n  - Parses stream-json output for completion/needs-input/error status\n  - Writes `status.json` with exit code, completion status, error details\n  - Commits remaining changes, pushes branch\n  - Creates PR via `gh` if requested\n  - Commits agent output log\n  - Comments prompt on PR\n  - Runs self-review phase with reduced budget (20% minimum $2)\n  - Extracts PR URL and posts review as comment\n\n### `scripts/` - Operational Helpers\n- **create-task.sh** - CLI to submit tasks:\n  - Accepts repo_url and prompt as positional args\n  - Flags: --branch, --target-branch, --model, --effort, --budget, --runtime, --turns, --pr, --pr-title, --pr-body, --claude-md, --context, --self-review, --env\n  - Posts JSON payload to `/api/v1/tasks`\n\n- **setup-aws.sh** - One-time infrastructure setup:\n  - Creates ECR repository\n  - Creates IAM role with SSM and ECR policies\n  - Creates instance profile\n  - Creates security group (outbound-only)\n  - Creates launch template with user-data script\n  - Auto-detects AMI based on instance type architecture\n  - Outputs launch template ID for .env\n\n- **db-status.sh** - Database inspection:\n  - Dumps all tasks with status summary\n  - Dumps all instances with status summary\n  - Uses sqlite3 queries\n\n- **user-data.sh** - EC2 instance bootstrap:\n  - Installs Docker and SSM agent\n  - Authenticates with ECR using IMDSv2\n  - Pulls backflow-agent image\n\n### `docs/` - Documentation\n- **schema.md** - SQLite schema reference:\n  - `tasks` table (28 columns with defaults and descriptions)\n  - `instances` table (8 columns)\n  - Status lifecycles\n  - Timestamp handling, JSON serialization\n  - Migration strategy\n\n- **file-reference.md** - Complete file reference guide (all files listed with descriptions)\n\n### Database Schema\n**Tasks table:**\n- Primary key: `id` (ULID with `bf_` prefix)\n- Status, repo/branch info, prompt, config (model, effort, budget, runtime, turns)\n- PR info, allowed_tools, custom CLAUDE.md, env_vars\n- Execution info: instance/container IDs, retry_count, cost, error\n- Timestamps: created_at, updated_at, started_at, completed_at\n- Indexes on status and created_at\n\n**Instances table:**\n- Primary key: `instance_id`\n- Instance type, availability zone, private IP\n- Status, max/running container counts\n- Timestamps: created_at, updated_at\n- Index on status\n\n### Architecture Summary\n**Two operating modes:**\n1. **EC2 mode (default)** - Spot instances with SSM for docker execution\n2. **Local mode** - Docker on local machine\n\n**Two auth modes:**\n1. **api_key** - Concurrent agents (multi-tenant)\n2. **max_subscription** - Serial execution (single agent at a time)\n\n**Two goroutines:**\n1. REST API on `:8080` (chi router)\n2. Orchestrator poll loop (5s default interval)\n\n**Flow:** Client → API → SQLite → Orchestrator → Docker on EC2 via SSM (or local) → Webhooks\n\n### Absolute File Paths\n```\n/home/agent/workspace/CLAUDE.md\n/home/agent/workspace/README.md\n/home/agent/workspace/Makefile\n/home/agent/workspace/.env.example\n/home/agent/workspace/.gitignore\n/home/agent/workspace/go.mod\n/home/agent/workspace/go.sum\n/home/agent/workspace/prompts.md\n/home/agent/workspace/cmd/backflow/main.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/api/handlers.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/api/handlers_test.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/api/server.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/api/responses.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/config/config.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/models/task.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/models/task_test.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/models/instance.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/notify/webhook.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/ec2.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/docker.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/scaler.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/spot.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/orchestrator/local.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/store/store.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/store/sqlite.go\n/home/agent/workspace/internal/store/sqlite_test.go\n/home/agent/workspace/docker/Dockerfile\n/home/agent/workspace/docker/entrypoint.sh\n/home/agent/workspace/scripts/create-task.sh\n/home/agent/workspace/scripts/setup-aws.sh\n/home/agent/workspace/scripts/db-status.sh\n/home/agent/workspace/scripts/user-data.sh\n/home/agent/workspace/docs/schema.md\n/home/agent/workspace/docs/file-reference.md\n```\n\nThis is a complete, production-grade Go service with 36 Go/shell files across 8 main directories, WAL-mode SQLite persistence, AWS EC2 integration, Docker orchestration, webhooks, and a comprehensive REST API."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac862f08d156bd849 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54937\ntool_uses: 30\nduration_ms: 68130</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a2b6d02e-3c8e-471d-894d-da47ffea5542","uuid":"de6e0f1b-9e22-475f-9bc3-56067d3f4dd1","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the repository at /home/agent/workspace. I need a complete picture of every file and directory. Please:\n\n1. List all files recursively (excluding .git directory, vendor, node_modules)\n2. For each Go file in internal/, give me a brief summary of what it contains (key types, functions, interfaces)\n3. For files in docker/, summarize what each file does\n4. List all files in the root directory\n5. List all files in docs/\n6. List any other directories and their contents\n\nBe very thorough - I need to know about every file in the repo.","agentId":"ac862f08d156bd849","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture of the repository. Let me compile a comprehensive summary.\n\n## Complete Repository Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Backflow repository. Here's a comprehensive breakdown of every file and directory:\n\n### Root Directory Files\n- **CLAUDE.md** - Project instructions for Claude Code with architecture overview, commands, and design patterns\n- **README.md** - Complete project documentation with quickstart, API reference, configuration, and examples\n- **Makefile** - Build targets: `build`