nning()` (status checks, timeouts, completions), `dispatchPending()` (assign tasks to instances), `scaler.Evaluate()`\n  - Handles task completion, failure, cancellation\n  - Tracks container counts per instance\n  - Implements `LogFetcher` interface for API logs\n\n- **scaler.go** - EC2 auto-scaling:\n  - Defines `scaler` interface (`Evaluate`, `RequestScaleUp`)\n  - `Scaler` implementation for EC2: launches spot instances, waits for SSM + Docker readiness\n  - `isSSMReady()` checks SSM agent status\n  - `isDockerReady()` verifies agent image availability\n  - Detects externally terminated instances\n  - Terminates idle instances after 5 minutes\n\n- **docker.go** - Container lifecycle via SSM (EC2) or local shell:\n  - `RunAgent()` builds `docker run` commands with task environment variables\n  - Sets up auth credentials (API key or Max subscription)\n  - Passes GitHub token, custom CLAUDE.md, env vars\n  - `InspectContainer()` checks state, reads `status.json`\n  - `StopContainer()` and `GetLogs()` wrap docker commands\n  - `runSSMCommand()` executes on EC2 instances via AWS SSM SendCommand\n\n- **ec2.go** - AWS EC2 wrapper:\n  - `LaunchSpotInstance()` creates one-time spot instances\n  - Uses launch template or AMI + instance type\n  - `TerminateInstance()` and `DescribeInstance()` wrap EC2 API calls\n  - Lazy-initializes AWS EC2 client\n\n- **local.go** - No-op scaler for local mode (no EC2 management needed)\n\n- **spot.go** - Spot interruption handler:\n  - `CheckInterruptions()` polls running instances for termination signals\n  - `handleInterruption()` marks instance as draining, re-queues running tasks as pending with incremented retry count\n\n### `internal/store/` - Persistence Layer\n- **store.go** - Store interface:\n  - Task CRUD: `CreateTask`, `GetTask`, `ListTasks`, `UpdateTask`, `DeleteTask`\n  - Instance CRUD: `CreateInstance`, `GetInstance`, `ListInstances`, `UpdateInstance`\n  - `TaskFilter` struct for list queries (status, limit, offset)\n  - `